replies.bodyText:
I think given you want to test the shared behaviour it's good to try and think hard about what the responsibility of onButtonClick really is here. For me what it does is ask for geo data for the widget. It feels to me like there could be an interface called something like GeoDataRequester or GeoDataFetcher with methods like requestPoint, requestShape etc:
binding.simpleButton.setOnClickListener(v -> {
    geoDataRequester.requestPoint(promp);
});

In each of the different geo widgets you can have a test that the requestPoint or whatever is called and then those methods can be tested for some implementation of the interface (ActivityGeoDataRequester).
Just to detail my questions here the though process I'm going through is:

I have shared code used in multiple places does it make sense to just test the behaviour in each place?
If not, what is the shared code responsible for? Is there some kind of interface/object/entity that could be responsible for that?

